          <tr><td><strong>Total 5-year cost</strong></td><td></td><td></td><td><strong>$199</strong></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p>That works out to about $40 per year for a keyboard that types as well as $200+ models. Compare that to a $40 membrane keyboard that needs replacement every 18 months — over 5 years you would spend $130+ and have a worse typing experience throughout.</p>

      <h3>What to Pair With Your Keyboard</h3>
      <p>A keyboard is only one part of your setup. Here are the accessories we recommend:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Mouse</strong> — the <a href="/reviews/logitech-mx-master-3s-review/">Logitech MX Master 3S</a> is our top pick. See our <a href="/reviews/best-wireless-mouse-work/">best wireless mouse for work</a> roundup for alternatives.</li>
        <li><strong>Desk pad</strong> — a <a href="/reviews/best-desk-pad-large/">large desk pad</a> reduces typing noise by 4 dB and protects your desk.</li>
        <li><strong>Standing desk</strong> — see our <a href="/reviews/best-standing-desk-under-300/">best standing desk under $300</a> guide.</li>
        <li><strong>Ergonomic chair</strong> — see our <a href="/reviews/best-ergonomic-chair-under-500/">best ergonomic chair under $500</a> guide.</li>
